[[File:Donishgohi agrarii Tojikiston.JPG|thumb|right|380px]]
'''Tajik Agrarian University Shirinsho Shotemur''' (TAU) ((Russian) ''Донишгоҳи аграрии Тоҹикистон'') is a university in [[Tajikistan]]. It is in [[Dushanbe]].

==History==
In 1931, the 'Central Asian Fruit-and-Vegetable Institute' was founded in the city of [[Khujand]] (former Leninabad). In 1934 it was reorganized and renamed into the 'Tajik Agricultural Institute'. In 1992, the Institute was again reorganized into 'Tajik Agrarian University'. The Government of Tajikistan decided (#311 from October 31, 2009{{citation needed|date=April 2013}}) to rename it as 'Tajik Agrarian University Shirinsho Shotemur'.<ref name=TAU>{{cite web|title=Tajik Agrarian University|url=http://www.tajagroun.tj/ru/|publisher=tajagroun.tj|accessdate=5 April 2013}}</ref>

==Academics==
TAU has a current enrolment of 6500 students.{{citation needed|date=April 2013}}

It has more than 35,000 alumni. There are nine faculties at the university: [[Agronomy]], [[Agribusiness]], Zoo-engineering, [[Veterinary science]], Economics, Horticulture and Biotechnology of Agriculture, Mechanization of Agriculture and Hydromeliorative methods, educating experts on 31 specialities.

