{{Infobox company | name = Paul A. Schmitt Music Company | logo = | type = Private | foundation = 1896 | location = [[Brooklyn Center]], [[Minnesota]], United States | key_people = | industry = [[Specialty Retail: Musical Instruments]] | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | num_employees = 400 | parent = | subsid = | products = [[Musical instrument]]s and accessories | homepage = [https://www.schmittmusic.com/ www.schmittmusic.com] | footnotes = }} '''Schmitt Music''' is an [[United States|American]] retail company which specializes in acoustic pianos, digital pianos, band and orchestra instruments, guitars and other [[musical instruments]], [[sheet music]] and accessories, as well as offering services such as instrument repair and [[Music education|music instruction]]. The company operates fourteen stores in seven states. Founded in [[1896 in music|1896]], it was awarded the [[Steinway & Sons]] Partners in Performance Award in [[2003 in music|2003]], and the Steinway & Sons "Dealer of the Year" in 2011. Schmitt Music was named Kawai Dealer of the Year in 2012.
